Ah ‚Äî now I see exactly where the confusion is. Let‚Äôs make this crystal clear in one go.

‚∏ª

1Ô∏è‚É£ Why IAM user can do S3 actions but Lambda cannot

Your setup:
	‚Ä¢	Bucket policy has:

"Deny": {
  "Principal": "*",
  "Action": "s3:*",
  "Condition": {
      "Bool": {"aws:SecureTransport": "false"},
      "StringNotEquals": {"aws:SourceVpce": "vpce-xxxx"}
  }
}

	‚Ä¢	IAM user is connecting via the VPCE ‚Üí matches the condition ‚Üí Deny does NOT apply ‚Üí IAM user‚Äôs Allow permissions work ‚Üí can Get/Put objects.
	‚Ä¢	Lambda is in the same VPC ‚Üí should also go through VPCE, but control-plane calls like DeleteBucketPolicy do NOT go through the VPCE.

Key point:
	‚Ä¢	IAM user uses the VPCE for data-plane operations (GetObject, PutObject) ‚Üí works
	‚Ä¢	Lambda attempts DeleteBucketPolicy (control-plane) ‚Üí VPCE not used ‚Üí aws:SourceVpce missing ‚Üí Deny triggers ‚Üí blocked
	‚Ä¢	IAM Allow cannot override Deny ‚Üí Lambda fails

‚úÖ So IAM user works because the request matches the VPCE condition. Lambda fails because control-plane requests ignore the VPCE.

‚∏ª

2Ô∏è‚É£ Can IAM user delete the bucket policy if allowed?

Yes ‚Äî IAM Allow can delete the bucket policy only if the bucket policy does not have a Deny that blocks this user.
	‚Ä¢	If bucket policy has no Deny on s3:DeleteBucketPolicy, then:

{
  "Effect": "Allow",
  "Action": "s3:*",
  "Resource": "*",
  "Principal": { "AWS": "arn:aws:iam::<ACCOUNT-ID>:user/<IAM-USER>" }
}

‚Üí The IAM user can delete the bucket policy.
	‚Ä¢	If bucket policy has a Deny (like the SourceVpce or SecureTransport deny), then even IAM user cannot delete unless the request satisfies the Deny condition.

‚∏ª

3Ô∏è‚É£ Bottom line

Principal	Action	Why it works or fails
IAM user	Get/Put	Works because IAM user request satisfies the bucket policy Deny conditions (via VPCE or public endpoint).
IAM user	DeleteBucketPolicy	Works only if bucket policy does not Deny it. If Deny exists, IAM Allow cannot override.
Lambda	DeleteBucketPolicy	Fails if bucket policy Deny exists (VPCE condition or other) because Lambda control-plane calls do not go through VPCE ‚Üí Deny triggers.
Lambda IAM policy	Add Allow	Alone cannot fix Deny ‚Üí must also add explicit Allow in bucket policy for Lambda role.


‚∏ª

‚úÖ Solution for Lambda
	1.	Add explicit Allow in the bucket policy for the Lambda role for:

s3:DeleteBucketPolicy
s3:PutBucketPolicy
s3:GetBucketPolicy

	2.	Keep existing Deny statements for all other principals.

